svg.title: F Skjerstadfjord & Aquaculture
svg.text: Skjerstadfjorden provides perfect living conditions for fish and other sea dwellers through perfect water quality given by the constant water exchange of the nearby Saltstraumen.Excellent water quality through low salinity concentration and high oxygen concentration because of the nearby Saltstraumen.The whole water amount of Skjerstadfjorden is being replaced in 150 days.
Survival time at different salinity concentrations
Sea lice concentrations in different fjords
The Sea lice concentration in Skjerstadfjorden is very low

No rapid water temperature changesNo temperatures over 15°C-> salmon development would speed up too fast ; this can cause defects and death and also increases the biological wasteNo temperatures below low plus degrees-> development would slow down
Optimal Oxygen levels are between 85% and 120%
